description._content: Catalog #: 09_01578 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Keystone LB-7 aircraft in flight above hangars. Invitation reads ""The air Corps Advanced Flying School requests the honor of your presence at the Graduation Excercises at Kelly Field, Texas, June 29, 1933. Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Corporation Name: Keystone Aircraft Tags: Elwyn H.
